----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
level 1-Basic transposition - Reverse cipher

The reverse cipher is a very simple and weak method of encryption.  Each letter is simply put in reverse order.
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
cipher text: dlo mi nehw trohs mi dna gnuoy mi nehw llat mi
plain text: im tall when im young and im short when im old
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
level 2-transposition - rail fence cipher

A transposition cipher works by moving and rearraning letters.  The rail fence cipher etc etc
[img]example image[/img]
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
cipher text: WACMS ONUNV ROSPH TOEDW BTEEG EUA
plain text: what comes down but never goes up
